If you only knew! In some ways this is a dream come true. Not only because jazz is my true musical background, the only thing my dad played in the house. It’s the genre i absorbed daily my entire childhood.  It is an honour to play tribute to two such Icons as Nat King Cole and Natalie Cole in this way and in this manner. 

In Honor of Black History Month…
I am happy to announce i am co producing a tribute called the Cole Legacy Experience honouring the great late Nat King Cole and his daughter Natalie Cole.  Thank you to help of my mentor and friend Horace Alexander Young, Alex Navarro, Sharon Montgomery, The Houston Professional Musicians Union, Eileen Morris of the Ensemble Theatre made possible by the Musicians Performance Trust fund. 

The event takes place Monday February 6th at 7 pm at the Ensemble Theatre. It is free ya’ll!!

This is a facebook livestream event. Link in bio….

We are excited to also feature a 22 piece orchestra of some of Houston’s finest musicians…..so please share the evening with us. If not feel free to watch via livestream…

Honoured, Excited, Proud and Humbled!

See you there!
@alexnavarromusic @afmlocal65699 @the.mptf @tet_houston

This past year i started teaching at Humphrey School of Musical Theatre at Theatre Under the Stars and i have loved every single second. My students have excelled at every thing i throw at them. The dedication i see in them is inspiring. Art saves lives. To see them be inspired and get that “lightbulb” moment is truly awesome. We are working on our own recording of Seasons of Love from the iconic musical Rent. Since i was forced to become my own engineer in 2020 i have been able to implement recording into my teachings. These kids are kicking butt and taking names. I can’t wait for you all to hear what we have been doing!

It had been a truly inspiring week in Houston the last couple of weeks!  First and foremost if you all do not know about @diazmusicinstitute in houston you truly are missing out. This is one of the best programs for young people in the country. This music is also just everything, truly my roots. I am grateful to be on staff periodically with this incredible program as a vocal director and instructor. So inspiring to see my mentees grow and step up to the plate and claim their moment. I was completely blown away by @joey_music_inc @lilybravo.plays @thisisjasmin.e @_kirstenn._ shining their light so bright with icon @officialhubertlaws and houston legend @locrian67_ ! These guys killed it. 

Hubert Laws (a native houstonians) is an American flutist and saxophonist with a career spanning four decades. He is one of the few classical artists who has also mastered jazz, pop and R&B . He has three Grammy nominations! This piece is called “Medias Negras” a composition written by Hubert with the chart written by Horace Alexander Young.

During the height of the pandemic in 2020, I, like a lot of vocalists was forced to adapt to the new normal and learned how to engineer and record and basically run my own recording studio.  My creativity flowed around that time with the luxury of time and exploration i finally wrote and produced a bunch of new songs…i then released these songs on an EP called Weep Willow.  These songs will forever represent that moment we were all in then….the amazing blessing is that i now work in My home studio regularly recording, arranging and producing vocals for dozens of clients including Grammy winners, Oscar winners and credible independent artists as well as voice overs. I love it!!

I am beyond grateful that my original music has inspired new colleagues of mine who produce variety or cabaret shows. Tomorrow 5/31 a new show will premiere @ostorahouston and it will feature me singing my song Weep Willow and Eye in th Sky off my EP Weep Willow…..i hope you will join us.

We are just a few days away from this amazing event that i get to be a part of! I am grateful to be surrounded by such amazing talent and new friends and colleagues that i cherish. It is a. Honour to be a special guest at this years Texas Southern University’s Homecoming event. It will be my first time performing at the historic Eldorado Ballroom.  The Eldorado Ballroom was developed by entrepreneur Clarence Dupree and his wife Anna Dupree , two African american business people. It’s main goal was to establish a community entertainment venue for black social clubs in Houston’s third ward neighborhood. It was built in 1939. It was the only place where African Americans could play music for a long time….

The Eldorado Ballroom recently underwent a massive investment for a renovation..

To give you some perspective my hero Ella Fitzgerald played this room along with other icons who heavily influenced me like BB King, James Brown and Ray Charles…

I love history ! So this is exciting for me and i am grateful….also to be surrounded such great talent on Friday..

See you there!

The first time i smelled authentic real OUD incense was in Qatar in 2007 when i flew there in a private jet with Enrique, band and management. We were doing a concert there for the Qatar Foundation. This trip started a whole new chapter in my life and Qatar is the catalyst for me appreciating the beauty and culture of the Middle East. Smelling OUD incense for the first time was unreal. I then got introduced to OUD perfume, perfume made from OUD, far less chemicals than western perfume. This is the highest quality perfume yo i can buy. The essential oil made from OUD is some of the most expensive in the world….

Gratefully you can now buy authentic Arabian oud in a few big cities in America now! It is the best and literally makes me feel like i am a queen, a goddess and a divine one at that!

This is literally my favorite perfume in the world! And yet there are so many good ones under this brand..

Check it out!!

This is my Confession….

It has been an amazing year, with ups and downs and hills and valleys. I have laughed so hard and cried so hard. I have been tested in new ways, i have been excited, i feel accepted, at times i have felt defeated and confused. I am developing new relationships with people because of who they are and not what they can give me. I have been forced to re-evaluate some things, people and circumstances. I have learned things, tapped into a deeper understanding of who i am , where i need to go and things i need to avoid. Through it all i will always be an optimist despite life’s challenges. I believe in the good inside me and inside you …..even if i have not met YOU specifically…..i feel tapped into my purpose and worth more than ever….change is humbling.

It’s the holiday season…..it is supposed to be a season of joy. Remember your actions can help bring someone joy or even sadness. Be mindful. Be kind, be patient and give fearlessly……don’t always worry about the return, if you believe in God, you know your every move is being watched….
